---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Rastion • Contribute" description="How to add an executable TSP solver to the Rastion routing hub.">
  <section class="card">
    <p class="kicker">Contribution Contract</p>
    <h1>Add A TSP Solver</h1>
    <p>
      Phase 1 listings require more than a claim. A solver must have a valid card, a working adapter, and official TSP
      suite outputs so the catalog stays reproducible and useful to the routing community.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid cards" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>1. Add the adapter</h2>
      <p>Create a local plugin under <code>plugins_local/</code> that exposes <code>get_solver()</code> and supports <code>tsp</code>.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>2. Add the solver card</h2>
      <p>Create <code>catalog/solvers/&lt;solver-id&gt;/card.json</code> plus a short <code>README.md</code> detail file.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>3. Validate the catalog</h2>
      <pre><code>python -m rastion validate-cards</code></pre>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>4. Run the official suites</h2>
      <pre><code>python -m rastion eval-suite tsplib-small-v1
python -m rastion eval-suite tsplib-medium-v1
python -m rastion eval-suite tsplib-large-v1</code></pre>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>5. Build site artifacts</h2>
      <pre><code>python -m rastion build-site-data</code></pre>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>6. Submit the PR</h2>
      <p>Include the adapter, solver card, and generated artifacts. Explain the method class, limits, and failure modes honestly.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <h2>Listing Rules</h2>
    <ul class="list-reset">
      <li>Phase 1 public listings are TSP only.</li>
      <li>Routing is the umbrella story, but VRP support is roadmap work until the interfaces expand.</li>
      <li>Official suites are curated and suite-scoped. There is no single global routing leaderboard.</li>
      <li>Experimental listings are allowed, but dependency and coverage gaps must remain visible.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
